“Alverno’s 8 Abilities give us the tools necessary to reach our full potential in                            the workplace. As students, we practice them daily in our lives, in the classroom                            and in our internships. By the time we graduate, we’re ready for whatever comes next.”
Alverno and the Montessori Institute of Milwaukee are partnering to meet growing demand for this dynamic style of learning.
Joseph Foy, Ph.D., Named Vice President of Academic Affairs  at Alverno College

Joseph Foy, Ph.D., has been named vice president of Academic Affairs at Alverno College. Foy, who is currently dean of the College of Arts, Sciences and Letters at Marian University in Fond du Lac, Wis., begins his appointment April 15.

The best way to discover if Alverno is right for you is to come see – and try for                      yourself – at our interactive preview day event (April 4). Discover how what makes                      us different will help YOU stand out.

Our admissions application is easy to complete. Although there isn’t an application                      deadline, it
s important to submit your application as soon as possible to remain eligible for                      academic scholarships and other financial assistance.
Submit ACT score and high school transcript

Include Alverno among the list of colleges receiving your score or contact ACT for                      details on how to send your scores. We’ll also need a copy of your official transcripts.                      Check with your guidance counselor on how to submit.
The 2020-21 FAFSA is now available. If you have any questions, feel call 414-382-6046                      for a phone consultation or in-person appointment with our financial aid team.

Residing on campus isn’t required, but it is a great way to enjoy convenient access                      to classes, a full calendar of activities and a supportive community. Learn more about                      living on campus.
New students should plan on submitting a $100 confirmation deposit to hold your spot                      for the upcoming semester.
Once you’re accepted, you’ll receive more information about attending Student Orientation                      And Registration (SOAR).
